They are both the assholes here. Bro im the fatass that loves/is addicted to food too in my fit friend group too. But im not a big fan anymore of culcuts or sandwhiches or party subs. So ill have one or two at most sometimes not even. The ones people bring to parties where i live either aren't that good or are good but have usually been sitting out for damn near the whole day in the sun/night by the time i get their so they are a little soggy and nasty and unappealing to me and my personal taste by that point but i know thats just me being picky cause plenty dont mind them like that and even like them like that. So maybe that's why i cant fathom it. 

But idk how you can eat over 4 feet of a 6 feet sub in one sitting and again im a fatass that loves food too but theres literally 36 sandwhiches in a 6 foot sub, and as ethan said he ate more then 3 feet, but lets be generous and say he ONLY ate 3 feet meaning only half of it.....thats still.....literally.......At minimum.....18 fucking sandwhiches.....in one sitting.....

I completely disagree with the hosts calling him out and making a huge scene about it and being big assholes about it making it a huge issue thats really fucked up and they are def assholes/the asshole for that. BUT AT THE SAME TIME hes also absolutely an asshole/the asshole for eating 18 sandwhiches (again thats being generous it was more) in one sitting, half of which were for other people, in the first hour of a party thats meant to be hours and hours long that is fucking wild and thats coming from a fellow fatass that loves and is addicted to food. 

the friends texting him the next morning saying you need to get your shit together/in order/under control aren't wrong. 18 plus sandwhiches in one sitting half of which are meant for others is wild 

( "i waited an hour so i thought everyone lost interest." Every party i've ever been to the party is literal hours and hours long to potentially the entire day/night the sub usually isn't meant to be the main meal at a party its meant to be picked on throughout the night/party that's literally the entire point of it. its doesn't need to be/isn't meant to be rushed through and fully eaten within the first hour of like a 6 plus hour party lol.
